verse_content.Word_by_word:
iṣṭān—desired; bhogān—necessities of life; hi—certainly; vaḥ—unto you;
devāḥ—the demigods; dāsyante—award; yajña-bhāvitāḥ—being satisfied by the
performance of sacrifices; taiḥ—by them; dattān—things given; apradāya—
without offering; ebhyaḥ—to the demigods; yaḥ—he who; bhuṅkte—enjoys;
stenaḥ—thief; eva—certainly; saḥ—is he.
